title: Claim for loss of notice pay

heading_context: Claim for loss of notice pay
chunks.html_content: Use this service to claim money if your employer is insolvent and you have not been paid for your notice period (‘statutory notice pay’). This includes if you did not work your notice period.
chunks.plain_content:
Claim for loss of notice pay 
Use this service to claim money if your employer is insolvent and you have not been paid for your notice period (‘statutory notice pay’). This includes if you did not work your notice period.

heading_context: Claim for loss of notice pay
chunks.html_content: You must apply for redundancy and any other money you’re owed first - even if you’re not owed any money. You’ll then get an email to say when you can start your claim for loss of notice.
chunks.plain_content:
Claim for loss of notice pay 
You must apply for redundancy and any other money you’re owed first - even if you’re not owed any money. You’ll then get an email to say when you can start your claim for loss of notice.

heading_context: Claim for loss of notice pay
chunks.html_content:
You’ll need:

  • your National Insurance number
  • an ‘LN’ claim reference number (you’re sent this after you claim for redundancy)
  • details of any money you earned during your notice period
  • details of any unemployment benefits you claimed during your notice period (if you did not claim any you’ll need to explain why)
